arts.ttl: Chris Davies reacts as Birmingham City rocked by double injury blow in Wycombe win
arts.sum: Injuries continue to bite Birmingham City after Ryan Allsop and Ethan Laird limped off during the 1-0 win over Wycombe Wanderers. Ryan Allsop and Ethan Laird hobbled off during Birmingham City's win over Wycombe Wanderers

arts.ttl: Birmingham City player ratings after Taylor Gardner-Hickman seals enormous Wycombe win - Alex Dicken
arts.sum: Blues managed the game in the second half and despite having to contend with injuries to key players Laird and Allsop, they never looked like conceding. Taylor Gardner-Hickman scored the only goal of the game to extend Blues’ unbeaten run in League One to 18 matches and put 12 points worth of breathing space between themselves and the chasing pack.

arts.ttl: Wycombe win shows Chris Davies’ Birmingham City are racing in one direction
arts.sum: Now that Blues have 76 points from 32 matches, they are only five wins away from the magic 90 – a total which almost always sees teams promoted from League One. Blues’ win over Wycombe means they are now tracking for 109 points over this 46-game season – a total that would see them eclipse not only the League One points record, but the EFL one too.

arts.ttl: Birmingham beat second-placed Wycombe to go 12 points clear at League One summit
Chris Davies reveals Krystian Bielik talks after benching Birmingham City captain
arts.sum: Chris Davies has moved to reassure Krystian Bielik that he has "a big role to play" now that the Birmingham City captain is on the fringes of the first XI. He’s a very important player who can play different positions, and I’m sure that he will find his way back into the team at some point.”

arts.ttl: Birmingham City set for injury boost as Chris Davies gives Stansfield and Anderson latest
arts.sum: Marc Leonard could bolster Birmingham City’s squad after three weeks out with a knee injury – but Chris Davies has ruled top scorer Jay Stansfield and influential winger Keshi Anderson out of the Wycombe clash.
